{"schema_version":"1.7.3","id":"OESA-2025-2001","published":"2025-08-15T12:39:21Z","modified":"2025-09-03T06:31:11.571742Z","upstream":["CVE-2024-2467"],"summary":"perl-Crypt-OpenSSL-RSA security update","details":"encoding and decoding according to using the openSSL libraries\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nA timing-based side-channel flaw exists in the perl-Crypt-OpenSSL-RSA package, which could be sufficient to recover plaintext across a network in a Bleichenbacher-style attack. To achieve successful decryption, an attacker would have to be able to send a large number of trial messages. The vulnerability affects the legacy PKCS#1v1.5 RSA encryption padding mode.(CVE-2024-2467)","affected":[{"package":{"name":"perl-Crypt-OpenSSL-RSA","ecosystem":"openEuler:24.03-LTS-SP2","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/perl-Crypt-OpenSSL-RSA&distro=openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP2"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"0.35-1.oe2403sp2"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"aarch64":["perl-Crypt-OpenSSL-RSA-0.35-1.oe2403sp2.aarch64.rpm","perl-Crypt-OpenSSL-RSA-debuginfo-0.35-1.oe2403sp2.aarch64.rpm","perl-Crypt-OpenSSL-RSA-debugsource-0.35-1.oe2403sp2.aarch64.rpm","perl-Crypt-OpenSSL-RSA-help-0.35-1.oe2403sp2.aarch64.rpm"],"src":["perl-Crypt-OpenSSL-RSA-0.35-1.oe2403sp2.src.rpm"],"x86_64":["perl-Crypt-OpenSSL-RSA-0.35-1.oe2403sp2.x86_64.rpm","perl-Crypt-OpenSSL-RSA-debuginfo-0.35-1.oe2403sp2.x86_64.rpm","perl-Crypt-OpenSSL-RSA-debugsource-0.35-1.oe2403sp2.x86_64.rpm","perl-Crypt-OpenSSL-RSA-help-0.35-1.oe2403sp2.x86_64.rpm"]},"database_specific":{"source":"https://repo.openeuler.org/security/data/osv/OESA-2025-2001.json"}}],"references":[{"type":"ADVISORY","url":"https://www.openeuler.org/zh/security/security-bulletins/detail/?id=openEuler-SA-2025-2001"},{"type":"ADVISORY","url":"https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2024-2467"}],"database_specific":{"severity":"Medium"}}